P(z) = z^n + a_{n−1}z^{n−1} + \cdots + a_1z + a_0
n > 0
\lvert P(z) \lvert \le 1
\lvert z \rvert = 1
P(z) = z^n
\dfrac{P(z)}{z^n}
z^n - \varepsilon\, P(z)
n
\varepsilon \in (0, 1)
0 \leq \frac{\varepsilon \,|a_k|}{1-\varepsilon} \leq {n \choose k}
k \in \{0, \dotsc, n-1\}
0 \leq |a_k| \leq \frac{1-\varepsilon}{\varepsilon}{n \choose k}.
\varepsilon \to 1
